  <section>
    <h2>embed vs. object</h2>
    <p>The key difference is fallback content. <code>&lt;embed&gt;</code> is a void element with no closing tag, so it cannot contain alternative markup. <a href="/docs/elements/native/object/"><code>&lt;object&gt;</code></a> supports content between its tags that is displayed when the resource fails to load.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Comparison: embed, object, and img">{{ objectAlternativeCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>For any use case where the resource might not load, prefer <code>&lt;object&gt;</code> or a native element over <code>&lt;embed&gt;</code>.</p>
  </section>

