  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;embed&gt;</code> element has significant accessibility limitations:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>No fallback content mechanism -- if the resource cannot be loaded, the user gets nothing</li>
      <li>No native <code>alt</code> attribute like <code>&lt;img&gt;</code></li>
      <li>Embedded content is opaque to screen readers unless the content itself is accessible</li>
      <li>Prefer elements with built-in accessibility semantics (<code>&lt;img&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;video&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;audio&gt;</code>) whenever possible</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

